1. ETHICAL USE RESTRICTION

   The Software SHALL NOT be used, in whole or in part, directly or
   indirectly, for any of the following purposes:

   a. MASS SURVEILLANCE — Any system designed to monitor, track, profile,
      or aggregate data on populations or groups of individuals without
      their informed, voluntary consent. This includes but is not limited
      to facial recognition systems, behavioral prediction at scale,
      social credit scoring, communications interception, and location
      tracking infrastructure.

   b. LAW ENFORCEMENT — Any system operated by or on behalf of police,
      prosecutors, courts, corrections, probation, parole, or any other
      entity exercising criminal justice authority. This includes but is
      not limited to predictive policing, criminal risk assessment,
      recidivism prediction, interrogation assistance, evidence analysis
      for prosecution, immigration enforcement, and border surveillance.

   c. MILITARY — Any system operated by or on behalf of armed forces,
      defense agencies, intelligence agencies, or military contractors.
      This includes but is not limited to weapons systems (autonomous or
      otherwise), targeting systems, intelligence gathering, reconnaissance,
      battlefield analysis, drone operations, cyber warfare, and any
      application designed to cause, facilitate, or optimize the use of
      force against human beings.

   d. DERIVATIVE RESTRICTION — Any derivative work, fork, modification,
      or system incorporating substantial portions of the Software is
      bound by these same restrictions. These restrictions cannot be
      removed, waived, or circumvented by relicensing.

2. PERMITTED USES

   Subject to the restrictions in Section 1, the Software may be freely
   used for any purpose, including but not limited to:

   - Academic and independent research
